 accepted principles of the Greeks. Though the links have gone unrecognized, the American radical tradition stems not from Aristotle, he maintains, but from the prophets of the Hebrew Bible.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jun 2020) 0aEnglish languagezUnited StatesxRhetoric. 0aEnglish language. 0aPolitical oratoryxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aPolitical oratory. 0aProphecyxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aProphecy. 0aRadicalismzUnited States. 0aRadicalism. 0aRhetoricxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aRhetoric. 0aSocial problemszUnited States. 0aSocial problems. 7aRELIGION / History.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814720981423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780814720981.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK